The paper deals with video processing and background/foreground separation, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of robust principal component analysis and matrix decomposition also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the importance of efficient algorithms, which could fall under mathematical optimization (cs.MM) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of ghosting effects, which could be related to signal processing (cs.SI).
